# mck3dprintfarm rules

- The test environment is an Alpine Linux docker container. Never use apt-get to obtain packages.
- Only push changes to github when asked by the user.
- Productione environment is also using docker. Make sure the docker container is repoducable on any system.
- We have a database versioning. When we add or remove features from the database make sure the version is updated. node scripts/create-migration.js "Add new feature XYZ"
- Moonraker printers use the moonraker-py API python library. 
- Prusa printers use the raw HTTP API endpoints.

- Goals for v0.0.4a is to have functional role based access with users.
- Goals for v0.0.5a is to add database backup functionallity to the UI and make an upgrade script that preserves the current database and updates it with any changes required.
- Goals for v0.0.6a is to have single sign on with Google and Entra ID working and using RBAC.
